cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.LG, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with computational topology and its application to machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on persistent homology and its effective computation suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The use of numerical methods and the mention of finite metric spaces suggest cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible category as well. The application to machine learning suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category, and the mention of distributed computation suggests cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category.
